@node "Human" "The Human race"


  The Humans.. A relatively young race that began it's evolution in the
 southern isles of Irall Rhin. The earliest known Human remains were
 found buried in the land surrounding the now mighty town of Vahrtaan.

  The Humans have built a strong empire in the south, where they are more
 common than the other races because of their shorter life-spans and quick
 breeding coupled with formidable force in numbers.

  The isles of Irall Rhin are not very safe though, and particularly in the
 south of Lyona, where Humans are thought to have originated from,
 barbarism is the norm. This has given Humans a rather bad reputation among
 other races who often think of them as a rather savage and 'pointless'
 race.. The equivalent of humanoid Goblins. Well, that's what many
 Dwarves think, as Humans aren't strong like a Dwarf, and they're pretty
 un-intelligent compared to Elves and the like. You can imagine what
 Dwarves think of Hill Dwarves..

  Never the less, Humans do have some advantages.. They are highly
 dexterous, and have speed and agility advantages over the stronger races.
 Granted, they aren't that intelligent in the scale of things, but they
 have a strong will, and are a lot more common than the other races in the
 South at least..

  Humans speak Common Tongue, and very rarely any other languages.


 Religion:

  1) The Creator - Worshipped by the Order of Nuln
  2) The Goddess of Law - Realzear
  3) The Sun - Balarh


